@PathVariable

Used to extract values from the URI path.

Typical for resource identifiers (e.g., /students/5).

Example:
@GetMapping("/students/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<Student> getStudentById(@PathVariable Long id) {
    return ResponseEntity.ok(new Student(id, "Alice", 22));
}

@RequestParam

Used to extract values from query parameters in the URL.

Typical for filters, search, optional values.

Example:
@GetMapping("/students/search")
public ResponseEntity<String> searchStudent(@RequestParam String name,@RequestParam(defaultValue = "18") int minAge) {
    return ResponseEntity.ok("Searching for " + name + " with min age " + minAge);
}